Avoid dividing systems into modules on the basis of flowcharts. Instead, begin
with a list of difficult design decisions or design decisions which are likely
to change. Each module is then designed to hide such a decision from the
others.[38;5;8m - David L. Parnas (1971) (paraphrased)[0m
%
