them mathematically.[38;5;8m - Leslie Lamport[0m
%
To think, you have to write. If you're thinking without writing, you only think
you're thinking.[38;5;8m - Leslie Lamport[0m
%
Writing requires thinking.[38;5;8m - Leslie Lamport[0m
%
There are two models of reality that I find to be the most useful ones,
especially when writing programs. The first is functions, and the second is
sequences of states.[38;5;8m - Leslie Lamport[0m
%
All possible successor states of any state.[38;5;8m - Leslie Lamport[0m
