%
Human practitioners are the adaptable element of complex systems. Some of these
adaptations include: (1) Restructuring the system in order to reduce exposure
of vulnerable parts to failure. (2) Concentrating critical resources in areas
of expected high demand. (3) Providing pathways for retreat or recovery from
expected and unexpected faults. (4) Establishing means for early detection of
changed system performance in order to allow graceful cutbacks in production or
other means of increasing resiliency.
[38;5;8m - Richard I. Cook, MD. 'How Complex Systems Fail'.[0m
