Customer Obsession: Start with the customer and work backwards. Work vigorously
to earn and keep customer trust. Pay attention to competitors, but obsess over
customers.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Ownership: Think long term and don't sacrifice long-term value for short-term
results. Act on behalf of the entire company, beyond just your own team. Never
say "that's not my job."[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Invent and Simplify: Expect and require innovation and invention from your
teams and always find ways to simplify. Be externally aware, look for new ideas
from everywhere, and don't be limited by "not invented here." As we do new
things, we accept that we may be misunderstood for long periods of time.
[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Right, A Lot: Have strong judgment and good instincts, seek diverse
perspectives and work to disconfirm your beliefs.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Learn and Be Curious: You are never done learning. Always seek to improve
yourself. Be curious about new possibilities and act to explore them.
[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Hire and Develop the Best: Raise the performance bar with every hire and
promotion. Recognize exceptional talent, and willingly move them throughout the
organization. Develop leaders and take seriously their role in coaching others.
Work on behalf of others to invent mechanisms for development.
[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Insist on the Highest Standards: Relentlessly high standards ‚Äî many people may
think these standards are unreasonably high. Continually raise the bar and
drive teams to deliver high quality products, services, and processes. Ensure
that defects do not get sent down the line and that problems are fixed so they
stay fixed.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Think Big: Thinking small is a self-fulfilling prophecy. Create and communicate
a bold direction that inspires results. Think differently and look around
corners for ways to serve customers.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Bias for Action: Speed matters. Many decisions and actions are reversible and
do not need extensive study. Value calculated risk taking.
[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Frugality: Accomplish more with less. Constraints breed resourcefulness, self-
sufficiency, and invention. No extra points for growing headcount, budget size,
or fixed expense.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Earn Trust: Listen attentively, speak candidly, and treat others respectfully.
Be vocally self-critical, even when doing so is awkward or embarrassing.
Benchmark yourself and your teams against the best.
[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Dive Deep: Operate at all levels, stay connected to the details, audit
frequently, and be skeptical when metrics and anecdote differ. No task is
beneath you.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Have Backbone; Disagree and Commit: Respectfully challenge decisions when you
disagree, even when doing so is uncomfortable or exhausting. Have conviction
and be tenacious. Do not compromise for the sake of social cohesion. Once a
decision is determined, commit wholly.[38;5;8m - Amazon leadership principle[0m
%
Deliver Results: Focus on key inputs and deliver them with quality and
timeliness. Despite setbacks, rise to the occasion and never settle.
